params.deployer: The address of the deployer to add.

allowSuckerDeployers(address[]).details: Can only be called by this contract's owner (initially project ID 1, or JuiceboxDAO).

params.deployers: The address of the deployer to add.

params.initialOwner: The initial owner of this contract.

deploySuckersFor(uint256,bytes32,(addres.details: The caller must be the project's owner or have `JBPermissionIds.DEPLOY_SUCKERS` from the project's owner.

params.configurations: The sucker deployer configs to use to deploy the suckers.
params.projectId: The ID of the project to deploy suckers for.
params.salt: The salt used to deploy the contract. For the suckers to be peers, this must be the same value on each chain where suckers are deployed.

returns.suckers: The addresses of the deployed suckers.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to get the suckers of.

returns.pairs: The pairs of suckers and their metadata.

params.addr: The address of the sucker to check.
params.projectId: The ID of the project to check for.

returns._0: flag A flag indicating if the sucker belongs to the project, and was deployed through this registry.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to get the suckers of.

returns._0: suckers The addresses of the suckers.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

PROJECTS().notice: A contract which mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.

allowSuckerDeployer(address).notice: Adds a suckers deployer to the allowlist.

allowSuckerDeployers(address[]).notice: Adds multiple suckers deployer to the allowlist.

deploySuckersFor(uint256,bytes32,(addres.notice: Deploy one or more suckers for the specified project.

getSuckerPairs(uint256).notice: Helper function for retrieving the projects suckers and their metadata.

isSuckerOf(uint256,address).notice: Returns true if the specified sucker belongs to the specified project, and was deployed through this registry.

suckerDeployerIsAllowed(address).notice: Tracks whether the specified sucker deployer is approved by this registry.

suckersOf(uint256).notice: Gets all of the specified project's suckers which were deployed through this registry.
